args: Ranzal has led a small force to the border\nof the Dyrenell Empire.
The prince sent them there in order to rescue\na number of civilian refugees.
Commander Ranzal, I have a report!
The refugees are being held up at a\nDyrenell checkpoint and can't reach us.
Also, our scouts report that the enemy\nnumbers eighty troops in all.
They've got more menâ€”but I'M here,\nwhich means we can still take 'em.
Normally that's what I'd do, but...
The guys at the checkpoint ain't attackin'\nthe civilians, which means we can't just\ngo chargin' in there ourselves.
Maybe this is a chance to show off\nmy newfound diplomacy!
Let us through! We seek refuge with\nPrince {player_name}!
The man you speak of is no longer\na legitimate prince of this nation.\nHe is a filthy traitor, nothing more.
And if you run to him, you will be\nbranded traitors also!
Then go back to where you came from\nbefore I clap the lot of you in irons!
But our village is being taxed too heavily\nfor us to make a living there!
Let none say I did not give fair warning.\n...Men! Arrest this rabble!
Huh? Who the devil are you?!

Ho there! I am Commander Ranzal of the
New Alberian Army, and I have come
thence and yon to make with thee a
parlay most heretofore!

Thus and verily, His Highness the Prince
did decree we hasten to save these
wretches, therefore have we hither
come to thee to grant forthwith succor!
I, uh, don't think he understood you, sir.\nYou sort of...mangled that.
Shut up! I ain't used to this kinda thing!
Ah, hell with it. I'm just gonna talk\nlike I always do.
Are you here to save us?
Fool! Do you think us so weak that we will\nhand these people over at your say-so?
I do not bandy words with traitors.\nTo arms, men!
Should we do the same, sir?
C'mon, now. We got no need for weapons\nand fightin'. Let's talk this thing out.
Ain't nobody wins if we all shut\neach other's eyes, yeah?
...But if ya won't negotiate, I'll beat\nya senseless until ya DO!
How can a man so vastly outnumbered\nproject such confidence...?
Uh, sir? I thought you said we were\ngoing to negotiate peacefully.
Nnngh! Sorry! Can't be losin' my cool like\nthat when I'm representin' New Alberia.
Look, these people wanna come to our\ncountry, and I think you should let 'em.
You think we should hand over imperial\ncitizens to an army of traitors?
Well, they clearly ain't happy to be\nin their current position.
If they have quarrel with the Empire,\nI shall relay that to my superiors.
Look, this probably ain't somethin' a\nnegotiator should be sayin'...
But the Empire don't seem like a place\nwhat's gonna take complaints seriously.
Ya REALLY wanna make 'em go back\nhome when they clearly don't want to?
Enough! I will not stand here and be\nlectured by the likes of you!
The rebellion of you treasonous snakes\nis what divided the country in the firstâ€”
Looks like we were yellin' a little\ntoo loudly there.
No way we can handle this many on our\nown. So the only way outta this...
Hey, Imperials! Give us a hand!\nWe'll beat these fiends back together!
I take no orders from rebel scum!
Is that REALLY yer top priority right now?!
We're talkin' about protectin' yer people,\nso drop the attitude and lend a hand.
I will do no such thing, dog! My soldiers\nand I can handle these fiends unaided.
Get into formation, men!\nWe will defeat these beasts!
Eh, all's well that ends well, I guess.
Good man. Meanwhile, I'm gonna help\nthe imperials with these fiends.
Though I admit your assistance was\nwelcome, I do not understand why\nyou came to our aid.
Regardless, you have my thanks for\nhelping to save our countrymen.
Don't worry about it. Er, so where ARE\nthose countrymen of yers, anyway?
They're not... Where did they go?!
Guess they ran off durin' the battle.
Which means we got nothin' else\nto talk about here.
You... You deliberately allowed them\nto escape during the battle!
Ain't sayin' I did...but ain't sayin'\nI didn't, neither.
I suppose you unleashed those fiends\nupon us as well!
Usin' fiends is what YOU do, not us.
Should we not have captured him, sir?
We were in no position for another fight\nafter the casualties we took earlier.

Besides, you saw how courageously he
fought those fiendsâ€”I'm not certain we
could have defeated him even if we all
took him on as one.
The sly devil knew just how to use the\nsituation to get the result he wanted.\nHe's obviously very experienced.
Glad yer all alive and kickin', too.
Thank you for saving us, sir!
Hell, we were just gonna keep\ngoin' in circles if we kept talkin'.
Looks like we actually owe a debt\nto the fiends for once. Bwa ha ha!
All right, let's get back ta the castle.
You must be really strong to take on\nthose fiends, mister.
Then why didn't you just beat up\nthose soldiers in the first place?
Then we could've come back to your\ncastle without all the trouble.
Because we had to prove somethin'.
We had to prove that New Alberia\nis doin' the right thing.
We do it because we believe\nit's the right thing to do.
But ya need more than just strength\nto prove yer on the side of right.
So that's why we try to talk to our enemies\ninstead'a just crackin' skulls.
We want everyone to know we ain't just\ngonna force folks to do what we want.
I want to live in your country all the more\nif it contains people like you.
Well, yer welcome to do so.
I get the feelin' you ain't the only folks\nwhat are gonna want to come here.
New Alberia will never turn its back\non people in need!
